provenance.note:
Probably inherited from Blake by his wife Catherine upon his death in 1827; 
                    probably acquired by Frederick Tatham upon Catherine Blake's death in 1831; 
                    sold anonymously, Sotheby's, 29 April 1862, in lot 166 with three other works by Blake (10s. to Richard Fisher, probably a dealer); 
                    apparently sold c. 1862 to the Royal Collection, now the Royal Collection Trust and housed at Windsor Castle, Berkshire, England.
